# Apple Pie

> Momâ€™s apple pie. The best apple pie ever! #dessert

Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

- Sugar | 1 cup | 
- Flour | 2 tbsp | 
- Cinnamon | 1 tsp | 
- Nutmeg | 1/8 tsp | 

Mix together the sugar, flour, cinnamon, and nutmeg.

- Apples | 4 cortland | 
- Apples | 4 macs | 

Peel and slice the apples.

Put the apple slices in a large bowl, mix in the flour / sugar mix and let sit while making the dough.

- Crisco | 2/3 cups | 
- Flour | 2 cups | 
- Salt | 1 tsp | 
- Water | 9 tbsp, divided  | 

Blend together the crisco, flour, and salt with the paddle attachment of your stand mixer.

Add water 1 tbsp at a time until you end up with a pliable dough.

Cut in half and till out half for bottom crust.

Fill with apples.

Roll out top crust and cover pie.

Make slots in top crusts and sprinkle with sugar.

Bake for 50-60 minutes.
